# Deobfuscated Code Analysis

## Deobfuscation

After resolving all the string lookups, base64 decoding, and control flow flattening, here's the clean version:

```javascript
var TWO_PI = Math.PI * 2;

// Configuration
var config = {
    repulsionK: 4000,       // Repulsion force constant
    springK: 0.004,         // Spring stiffness
    damping: 0.92,          // Velocity damping factor
    gravity: 0.0003,        // Centering gravity force
    particleMax: 40,        // Max number of particles
    particleFade: 0.04,     // Particle fade rate
    cameraEase: 0.06        // Camera easing factor
};

// Define nodes (graph vertices)
var nodes = [
    { id: "center", label: "Hub",      r: 26, x: 400, y: 300, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "alpha",  label: "Alpha",    r: 16, x: 500, y: 200, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "beta",   label: "Beta",     r: 16, x: 300, y: 400, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "gamma",  label: "Gamma",    r: 14, x: 250, y: 180, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "delta",  label: "Delta",    r: 14, x: 550, y: 380, vx: 0, vy: 0 },
    { id: "epsilon",label: "Epsilon",  r: 12, x: 350, y: 150, vx: 0, vy: 0 }
];

// Define edges (springs connecting nodes)
var edges = [
    { a: "center",  b: "alpha",   rest: 160, k: 0.006 },
    { a: "center",  b: "beta",    rest: 160, k: 0.005 },
    { a: "center",  b: "gamma",   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
    { a: "center",  b: "delta",   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
    { a: "center",  b: "epsilon", rest: 180, k: 0.003 },
    { a: "alpha",   b: "beta",    rest: 200, k: 0.002 },
    { a: "gamma",   b: "delta",   rest: 220, k: 0.002 },
    { a: "alpha",   b: "epsilon", rest: 200, k: 0.002 }
];

// Camera system
var camera = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };
var cameraTarget = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };

// Particles array and frame counter
var particles = [];
var frameCount = 0;

function findNode(id) {
    for (var i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        if (nodes[i].id === id) return nodes[i];
    }
    return null;
}

// Physics simulation step
function simulate() {
    // 1. Node-node repulsion (Coulomb's law)
    for (var i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        for (var j = i + 1; j < nodes.length; j++) {
            var dx = nodes[i].x - nodes[j].x;
            var dy = nodes[i].y - nodes[j].y;
            var dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
            var force = config.repulsionK / (dist * dist);
            var fx = (dx / dist) * force;
            var fy = (dy / dist) * force;
            nodes[i].vx += fx;
            nodes[i].vy += fy;
            nodes[j].vx -= fx;
            nodes[j].vy -= fy;
        }
    }

    // 2. Spring attraction along edges (Hooke's law)
    for (var i = 0; i < edges.length; i++) {
        var nodeA = findNode(edges[i].a);
        var nodeB = findNode(edges[i].b);
        if (!nodeA || !nodeB) continue;
        var dx = nodeB.x - nodeA.x;
        var dy = nodeB.y - nodeA.y;
        var dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
        var displacement = dist - edges[i].rest;
        var force = (edges[i].k || config.springK) * displacement;
        nodeA.vx += (dx / dist) * force;
        nodeA.vy += (dy / dist) * force;
        nodeB.vx -= (dx / dist) * force;
        nodeB.vy -= (dy / dist) * force;
    }

    // 3. Apply centering gravity, damping, and integrate velocity
    for (var i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        nodes[i].vx += (400 - nodes[i].x) * config.gravity;
        nodes[i].vy += (300 - nodes[i].y) * config.gravity;
        nodes[i].vx *= config.damping;
        nodes[i].vy *= config.damping;
        nodes[i].x += nodes[i].vx;
        nodes[i].y += nodes[i].vy;
    }
}

// Spawn a particle from a random node
function spawnParticle() {
    if (particles.length >= config.particleMax) return;
    var node = nodes[Math.floor(Math.random() * nodes.length)];
    var angle = Math.random() * TWO_PI;
    var speed = 0.3 + Math.random() * 0.7;
    particles.push({
        x: node.x,
        y: node.y,
        vx: Math.cos(angle) * speed,
        vy: Math.sin(angle) * speed,
        age: 0,
        maxAge: 800 + Math.random() * 1200,
        size: 0.8 + Math.random() * 1.2
    });
}

// Update all particles
function updateParticles() {
    for (var i = particles.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
        var p = particles[i];
        p.vx *= 0.995;
        p.vy *= 0.995;
        p.x += p.vx;
        p.y += p.vy;
        p.age++;
        if (p.age > p.maxAge) particles.splice(i, 1);
    }
}

// Ease camera toward target
function updateCamera() {
    camera.x += (cameraTarget.x - camera.x) * config.cameraEase;
    camera.y += (cameraTarget.y - camera.y) * config.cameraEase;
    camera.zoom += (cameraTarget.zoom - camera.zoom) * config.cameraEase;
}

// Main loop tick
function tick() {
    simulate();
    updateCamera();
    if (frameCount % 3 === 0) spawnParticle();
    updateParticles();
    frameCount++;
}

setInterval(tick, 16); // ~60 FPS
```

## What It Does

This is a **force-directed graph simulation engine**. Specifically:

1. **Graph Layout**: It simulates 6 nodes ("Hub", "Alpha", "Beta", "Gamma", "Delta", "Epsilon") connected by 8 spring edges, using a classic **spring-electric model**:
   - **Repulsion**: All nodes repel each other (inverse-square law, like electric charges)
   - **Spring attraction**: Connected nodes are pulled toward each other (Hooke's law with rest lengths)
   - **Centering gravity**: Gentle force pulling everything toward center (400, 300)
   - **Damping**: Velocity is multiplied by 0.92 each frame to prevent endless oscillation

2. **Particle Effects**: Every 3 frames, a decorative particle spawns from a random node, drifts outward slowly, and fades/dies after 800–2000 frames — purely cosmetic ambient effects.

3. **Camera System**: A smoothly-easing camera that interpolates toward a target position/zoom.

4. **Runs at ~60 FPS** via `setInterval(..., 16)`.

This is the **simulation/physics backend only** — there's no rendering code here. A separate module would read the node/particle positions and draw them to a canvas.
